	<title>
		Remove an account
	</title>

	<steps>
		<item>
			<p>Click the icon at the very right of the <gui>menu bar</gui> and select
			<gui>System Settings</gui>.
			</p>
		</item>

		<item>
			<p>Select <gui>Online Accounts</gui>.
			</p>
		</item>

    <item>
      <p>
        From the left windowpane, select the account you wish to remove.
      </p>
    </item>

    <item>
      <p>
        Click the <gui>Remove Account</gui> button in the lower-right portion of 
        the window.
			</p>

  <note style="tip">
    <p>
      Removing the selection from <app>Online Accounts</app> in no way affects
			the account from your service provider.
    </p>
  </note>
    </item>

    <item>
      <p>
        Click <gui>Remove</gui>.
      </p>
    </item>
  </steps>

  <note style="tip">
    <p>
      Instead of deleting the account completely, you can <link 
      xref="accounts-disable-service">restrict the service</link> from being
			accessed by your desktop.
    </p>
  </note>
